{{Infobox film | name = 3 Musketeers | image = 3musketeersdvd.jpg | alt = <!-- see WP:ALT --> | caption = DVD Cover | director = Cole McKay | producer = {{unbulleted list|[[David Michael Latt]]|[[David Rimawi]]|[[Paul Bales]]}} | writer = [[Edward DeRuiter]] | screenplay = | story = | based on = ''[[The Three Musketeers]]'' by [[Alexandre Dumas]] (uncredited) | starring = {{unbulleted list|[[Heather Hemmens]]|XIN|Alan Rachins|Keith Allan|[[Michele Boyd]]|David Chokachi}} | music = Chris Ridenhour | cinematography = [[Ben Demaree]] | editing = | studio = | distributor = [[The Asylum]] | released = {{Film date|2011|10|25}} | runtime = 90 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = $300,000 | gross = }} '''''3 Musketeers''''' is a [[direct-to-video]] [[Action film|action]] film by [[The Asylum]] loosely based on ''[[The Three Musketeers]]'' by [[Alexandre Dumas]]. The film is directed by Cole McKay and is a [[mockbuster]] that was released shortly after the [[Paul W. S. Anderson]] film ''[[The Three Musketeers (2011 film)|The Three Musketeers]]''. The film was released on DVD and [[Blu-ray disc]] on October 25, 2011.<ref name="Asylum">[http://www.theasylum.cc/blog/2011/06/from-the-set-3-musketeers/ The Asylum - From the Set: 3 Musketeers]</ref>
Unlike other adaptations of ''The Three Musketeers'', this film is a modern take on the original story.
== Plot == Set in the near-future United States, when junior NSA officer Alexandra D'Artagnan uncovers a plot by a corrupt general to assassinate the President of the United States to instigate a coup to take over the government in order to install a militarist regime, she enlists the help of three infamous international spies to stop the threat.
==Cast== *[[Heather Hemmens]] as Alexandra D'Artagnan *[[Xin Sarith Wuku|XIN]] as Athos *[[Keith Allan (actor)|Keith Allan]] as Porthos *[[Michele Boyd]] as Aramis *[[David Chokachi]] as Lewis *[[Darren Thomas]] as Rockford *[[Alan Rachins]] as Treville *[[Simon Rhee]] as a Commander *[[Andy Clemence]] as President King *[[Edward DeRuiter]] as Jenkins
