{{Infobox musical artist | name = Anthony Acid | image = | caption = | image_size = <!-- Only for images narrower than 220 pixels --> | background = non_vocal_instrumentalist | birth_name = Anthony Caputo | alias = Epocalips, Injection, Life Line, The Lil' DJ | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1965|4|2}} | death_date = | origin = [[Staten Island, New York|Staten Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States | instrument = | genre = [[House music|House]], [[Club music|Club]], [[Dance music|Dance]], [[Disco music|Disco]] | occupation = [[Disc jockey|DJ]], [[Music producer|Producer]], [[Remixer]] | years_active = | label = | associated_acts = Powerhouse, [[DJ Skribble]]
| website = [https://myspace.com/anthonyacid Anthony Acid] on [[Myspace]] }} '''Anthony Acid''' (born '''Anthony Caputo'''; April 2, 1965) is an American [[Disc Jockey|DJ]], [[Music Producer|producer]] and [[remixer]]. He has worked with the likes of Nast Nova,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DA8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA35&dq=%22Anthony+Acid%22&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=1#v=onepage&q=%22Anthony%20Acid%22&f=false|title=Dance Trax|last=Flick|first=Larry|date=26 April 1997|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=35|accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref> [[DJ Skribble]],<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1BAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA38&dq=%22Anthony+Acid%22&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=3#v=onepage&q=%22Anthony%20Acid%22&f=false|title=The Beat Box Hot Plate|last=Paoletta|first=Michael|date=27 April 2002|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=38|accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref> Brutal Bill,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NA0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA83&dq=%22Anthony+Acid%22&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=10#v=onepage&q=%22Anthony%20Acid%22&f=false|title=''Brutal Acid''|date=2 December 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=83|accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref> and Richie Santana.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bw4EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA20&dq=%22Anthony+Acid%22&lr=&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=12#v=onepage&q=%22Anthony%20Acid%22&f=false|title=''Marina''|date=6 June 1998|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|page=20|accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref>
