{{Infobox Organization |name = Radio Club Argentino |image = Radio_Club_Argentino_logo.png |image_border = |size = 85px |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = RCA |motto = |formation = October 21, 1921<ref name="rca_history"/> |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit organization]] |status = |purpose = Advocacy, Education |headquarters = |location = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] |region_served = [[Argentina]] |membership = |language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] |leader_title = President |leader_name = Carlos E. Beviglia LU1BCE |main_organ = |affiliations = [[International Amateur Radio Union]] |num_staff = |budget = |website = http://www.lu4aa.org/ |remarks = }}
The '''Radio Club Argentino''' ('''RCA''') (in [[English language|English]], literally '''Radio Club of Argentina''') is a national [[non-profit organization]] for [[amateur radio]] enthusiasts in [[Argentina]]. RCA was founded in [[Buenos Aires]] on October 21, 1921.<ref name="rca_history">Radio Club Argentino (2017). [https://www.lu4aa.org/wp/el-rca/]. Retrieved Jun. 03, 2017.</ref> Key membership benefits in the organization include the use of a [[QSL card|QSL]] bureau for those amateur radio operators in regular contact with amateur radio operators in other countries, a group [[insurance]] policy, and a quarterly membership journal called ''[[Revista del Radio Club Argentino]]''. The Radio Club Argentino represents the interests of Argentine amateur radio operators before Argentine and international regulatory authorities. It is also the national member society representing Argentina in the [[International Amateur Radio Union]].<ref name="iaru">International Amateur Radio Union (2008). [http://www.iaru.org/iaru-soc.html "Member Societies"]. Retrieved Aug. 1, 2008.</ref>
